r.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20country's%20unemployment%20rate%20also%20rose%20to%207.6%25%20in%20Q2%2C%20up%20from%206.2%25%20in%20the%20same%20period%20last%20year%2C%20according%20to%20Argentina's%20statistics%20agency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaria%20Victoria%20Murillo%2C%20director%20of%20the%20Institute%20of%20Latin%20American%20Studies%20at%20Columbia%20University%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musks-doge-looks-to-argentinas-economic-reform-cut-spending-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20BI%20last%20month%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20%26quot%3Bdeep%26quot%3B%20recession%2C%20while%20%26quot%3Bvery%20painful%2C%26quot%3B%20has%20been%20accepted%20by%20Argentinians%20because%20inflation%20was%20%26quot%3Bterrible%26quot%3B%20and%20people%20%26quot%3Bdo%20not%20want%20to%20go%20back.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20according%20to%20Argentina's%20statistics%20agency%2C%20the%20country's%20poverty%20rate%20rose%20to%2052.9%25%20in%20the%20first%20half%20of%202024%2C%20up%20from%2041.7%25%20in%20the%20second%20half%20of%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20the%20highest%20rate%20in%2030%20years%2C%20per%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FODSAUCA%2Fstatus%2F1849926722189131982%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eresearch%20team%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20Observatory%20of%20the%20Argentine%20Social%20Debt%2C%20which%20keeps%20track%20of%20key%20economic%20indicators.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20acknowledging%20declining%20inflation%2C%20it%20said%20growing%20poverty%20was%20a%20result%20of%20Milei's%20%26quot%3Bshock%26quot%3B%20economic%20plan%20and%20structural%20issues%2C%20including%20the%20devaluation%20of%20the%20peso.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFalling%20inflation%20%26quot%3Bdoes%20not%20yet%20translate%20into%20a%20greater%20capacity%20for%20household%20consumption%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22602738db-f424-45fd-b1f3-3b76a52aea08%5C%22%3EFiscal%20balance%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%2C%20however%2C%20some%20signs%20of%20recovery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20first%20five%20months%20of%202024%2C%20Argentina's%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbvaresearch.com%2Fen%2Fpublicaciones%2Fargentina-economic-outlook-june-2024%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eachieved%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20primary%20fiscal%20surplus%20of%201.1%25%20of%20GDP%20%E2%80%94%20its%20first%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmeetings.imf.org%2F-%2Fmedia%2FAMSM%2FFiles%2FSM2024%2FIMFC%2FArgentina.ashx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E12%20years%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20Milei's%20%26quot%3Bmost%20remarkable%20achievement%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Labaqui%20of%20Medley%20Global%20Advisors%2C%20who%20said%20the%20fiscal%20surplus%2C%20together%20with%20the%20exchange%20rate%20anchor%2C%20brought%20inflation%20down%20faster%20than%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbvaresearch.com%2Fen%2Fpublicaciones%2Fargentina-economic-outlook-october-2024%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBBVA%20Research%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20for%20its%20part%2C%20said%20that%20it%20expects%20Argentina's%20GDP%20to%20rebound%20strongly%20next%20year%2C%20from%20a%204%25%20deficit%20in%202024%20to%206%25%20in%202025%2C%20driven%20by%20investments%2C%20exports%2C%20and%20private%20consumption.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJuan%20Cruz%20D%C3%ADaz%2C%20managing%20director%20at%20Cefeidas%20Group%2C%20an%20international%20advisory%20firm%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20%26quot%3Bone%20year%20later%2C%20it%20can%20be%20argued%20that%20the%20economic%20landscape%20has%20certainly%20improved%2C%20although%20there%20is%20still%20a%20long%20way%20to%20go.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20Argentina%20is%20still%20expected%20to%20end%202024%20with%20an%20accumulated%20inflation%20of%20120%25%2C%20one%20of%20the%20highest%20in%20the%20world%2C%20but%20a%20sharp%20decline%20from%202023's%20211%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26q