expert%20and%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BHow%20Not%20to%20Be%20a%20People%20Pleaser%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20while%20constantly%20being%20on%20your%20toes%20may%20feel%20like%20a%20way%20to%20stay%20sharp%2C%20this%20mentality%20%26quot%3Bbreeds%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-of-toxic-workplace-how-identify-spot-interview-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etoxic%20work%20environment%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInstead%2C%20constant%20stress%20and%20fear%20of%20falling%20short%20can%20inspire%20anxiety%2C%20self-doubt%2C%20and%20burnout%20that%20is%20damaging%20to%20productivity%20and%20well-being%20alike%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228b2896af-d7db-4bd2-b6f6-4b7468d7a7f8%5C%22%3EA%20recipe%20for%20success%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBeck%20became%20the%20%26quot%3Bnewest%20space%20billionaire%26quot%3B%20in%20November%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Fmattdurot%2F2024%2F11%2F15%2Frocket-labs-founder-peter-beck-just-became-the-worlds-newest-space-billionaire%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20Forbes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20his%2010%25%20stake%20in%20Rocket%20Lab%20worth%20%24970%20million%2C%20and%20having%20accrued%20%2465%20million%20from%20selling%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20is%20currently%20valued%20at%20%2411.2%20billion%2C%20according%20to%20CNBC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20he%20is%20lagging%20behind%20other%20space%20entrepreneurs%2C%20including%20Elon%20Musk%20(worth%20%24354%20billion)%20with%20SpaceX%20and%20Jeff%20Bezos%20(worth%20%24240%20billion)%20with%20Blue%20Origin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERocket%20Lab's%20stock%20price%20surged%20to%20an%20all-time%20high%20at%20the%20end%20of%20November.%20While%20the%20company%20rivals%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-starlink-satellite-megaconstellation-harm-atmosphere-scientists-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMusk's%20SpaceX%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frocket-lab-ceo-peter-beck-interview-founder-mode-pan-gold-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBeck%20previously%20told%20BI%3C%2Fa%3E%20he%20has%20no%20intention%20of%20colonizing%20Mars.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20Rocket%20Lab%20focuses%20on%20building%20and%20managing%20rockets%20and%20satellites.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRocket%20Lab%20will%20never%20have%20the%20capital%20that%20Jeff%20and%20Elon%20have%2C%26quot%3B%20Beck%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2024-12-09%2Felon-musk-s-billionaire-rocket-rival-peter-beck-is-hustling-to-close-gap%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20Bloomberg%20News%20in%20an%20interview%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BBut%20all%20that%20means%20is%20you%20have%20to%20be%20a%20bit%20better%20at%20hustling%2C%20a%20little%20bit%20better%20at%20being%20innovative.%20You%20can't%20break%20the%20laws%20of%20physics%20no%20matter%20how%20much%20capital%20you've%20got.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c60be1cc-9435-40ef-9dd7-afc77d16348d%5C%22%3ECaution%20vs%20fear%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBeck%20believes%20that%20his%20paranoia%20and%20micromanaging%20have%20helped%20his%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20short%20term%2C%20paranoia%20and%20a%20hyper-vigilant%20mindset%20can%20drive%20exceptional%20results%2C%20Edel%20Holliday-Quinn%2C%20a%20business%20psychologist%20who%20has%20worked%20in%20senior%20roles%20at%20Citi%20and%20PwC%2C%20told%20BI%2C%20especially%20in%20high-stakes%20industries%20like%20aerospace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBreese%20Annable%2C%20a%20licensed%20clinical%20psychologist%20and%20career%20coach%20who%20has%20worked%20with%20many%20high-achieving%20professionals%2C%20also%20told%20BI%20that%20some%20level%20of%20alertness%20can%20be%20valuable%20for%20leaders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnticipating%20challenges%20and%20planning%20for%20contingencies%20are%20facets%20of%20strategic%20thinking%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20when%20vigilance%20crosses%20into%20chronic%20hypervigilance%2C%20the%20psychological%20and%20relational%20costs%20outweigh%20the%20benefits.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELamb%20told%20BI%20that%20leaders%20who%20are%20always%20anxious%20about%20the%20next%20misstep%20may%20lose%20sight%20of%20their%20own%20well-being.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20world%20thrives%20on%20fear%20%E2%80%94%20yeah%2C%20people%20take%20pride%20in%20their%20work%2C%20for%20sure%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BWanting%20to%20do%20good%20work%20is%20a%20fine%20goal.%20But%20if%20paranoia%20is%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20it%2C%20you%20are%20working%20to%20inhibit%20yourself%20rather%20than%20improve.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20difference%20between%20exercising%20caution%20and%20being%20immobilized%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwill-ferrell-on-finding-success-fear-of-failure-2017-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efear%20of%20failure%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Lamb%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRealistic%20caution%20is%20the%20practice%20of%20thinking%20about%20the%20future%2C%20having%20contingency%20plans%2C%20and%20being%20mindful%20of%20all%20of%20the%20hurdles%20we%20face%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20it's%20about%20managing%20those%20worries%20in%20a%20way%20that%20won't%20overwhelm%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a0e20f99-6b67-4211-a7c2-f40e835ad77a%5C%22%3ENegative%20impacts%20are%20individual%20and%20workplace-wide%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsleep-loss-deprivation-america-reasons-health-inequality-economic-stress-money-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESleep%20deprivation%3C%2Fa%3E%20significantly%20affects%20cognitive%20functioning%2C%20decision-making%2C%20and%20emotional%20regulation%2C%20Annable%20said%2C%20and%20if%20it%20is%20experience