ngs%20known%20as%20proxy%20statements.%20The%20documents%20include%20a%20breakdown%20of%20the%20salary%2C%20benefits%2C%20bonuses%2C%20and%20other%20perks%20to%20provide%20a%20dollar%20value%20of%20top%20executives'%20total%20compensation%20package%2C%20which%20must%20be%20approved%20by%20the%20board%20and%20shareholders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESecurity%20services%20paid%20for%20by%20the%20company%20for%20the%20benefit%20of%20an%20individual%20executive%20are%20typically%20included%20in%20a%20category%20called%20%26quot%3BOther%20Compensation%26quot%3B%20along%20with%20perks%20like%20personal%20corporate%20jet%20usage%2C%20401(k)%20matching%2C%20or%20tax%20preparation%20services.%20It's%20possible%20that%20some%20security%20costs%20may%20not%20be%20reported%20in%20proxy%20statements%2C%20particularly%20if%20they%20were%20paid%20for%20by%20the%20executives%20themselves%20and%20not%20reimbursed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c09eb59e-0f9e-4e25-ab58-39c299a8b9ff%5C%22%3EUnitedHealth%20Group's%20filings%20don't%20specify%20any%20personal%20security%20costs%20for%20Thompson%20last%20year%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20clear%20if%20Thompson%20had%20a%20security%20detail%20with%20him%20on%20the%20day%20of%20his%20death.%20Video%20footage%20obtained%20by%20the%20%3Cspan%3ENew%20York%20City%20Police%20Department%20appears%20to%20show%20him%20walking%20alone%20on%20his%20way%20into%20an%20%26quot%3Binvestor%20day%26quot%3B%20event%20in%20Manhattan.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20he%20was%20CEO%20of%20UnitedHealthcare%2C%20Thompson%20was%20also%20an%20executive%20vice%20president%20of%20UnitedHealth%20Group%2C%20for%20which%20he%20received%20%2421%2C187%20in%20other%20compensation%20in%202023.%20That%20amount%20represented%20%2414%2C850%20in%20401(k)%20matching%20and%20%246%2C337%20in%20health%20insurance%20premiums%2C%20with%20no%20amount%20indicated%20for%20personal%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20has%20yet%20to%20release%20its%20annual%20proxy%20statement%20outlining%202024%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELooking%20further%20up%20the%20corporate%20ladder%2C%20Thompson's%20boss%2C%20UHG%20CEO%20Andrew%20Witty%2C%20also%20did%20not%20receive%20payment%20for%20personal%20security%20as%20part%20of%20his%202023%20compensation%20package.%20However%2C%20the%20company%20did%20make%20corporate%20aircraft%20available%20for%20his%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223379%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Police%20scene%20in%20Manhattan%20outside%20the%20Hilton%20Hotel.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6750800def9a5d904789db5e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222534%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBrian%20Thompson%20was%20set%20to%20speak%20at%20an%20%26quot%3Binvestor%20day%26quot%3B%20event%20in%20Manhattan.%20The%20event%20was%20canceled%20after%20he%20was%20shot%20and%20killed%20while%20walking%20without%20personal%20security%20on%20the%20street.%3Cp%3EPaul%20Squire%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWitty%20is%20required%20for%20personal%20security%20reasons%20to%20use%20corporate%20aircraft%20for%20all%20business%20travel%20and%20is%20encouraged%20to%20use%20corporate%20aircraft%20for%20all%20personal%20travel%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20proxy%20statement%20says%2C%20adding%20that%20Witty%20did%20not%20make%20personal%20use%20of%20the%20company%20plane%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20UHG%20spokesperson%20told%20BI%20the%20company%20is%20%26quot%3Bpartnering%20with%20local%20law%20enforcement%20to%20ensure%20a%20safe%20work%20environment%20and%20reinforce%20security%20guidelines%20and%20building%20access%20policies.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECVS%2C%20which%20owns%20Aetna%2C%20does%20not%20disclose%20the%20compensation%20of%20Aetna's%20president.%20However%2C%20CVS%20did%20provide%20its%20former%20CEO%20Karen%20Lynch%20with%20%2444%2C148%20for%20%26quot%3Bpersonal%20protection%26quot%3B%20in%202023%2C%20as%20well%20as%20%24243%2C281%20for%20personal%20use%20of%20the%20company%20jet%20and%20%24106%2C086%20for%20personal%20use%20of%20a%20company%20car.%20A%20CVS%20spokesperson%20declined%20to%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECigna%20CEO%20David%20Cordani%20received%20%24310%2C437%20in%20%26quot%3Bother%20compensation%26quot%3B%20in%202023%2C%20largely%20constituted%20of%20%24178%2C704%20in%20personal%20travel%20on%20the%20company%20aircraft.%20Roughly%20%2495%2C000%20in%20other%20costs%20were%20provided%20for%20residential%20security%20system%20monitoring%20and%20maintenance%2C%20as%20well%20as%20expanded%20personal%20liability%20coverage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProxy%20statements%20for%20Humana%20and%20Elevance%20(owner%20of%20Anthem)%20did%20not%20specify%20personal%20security%20costs%2C%20while%20Kaiser%20Permanente%20is%20a%20nonprofit%20and%20not%20subject%20to%20the%20same%20reporting%20requirements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224c77ad76-96ee-4e7e-8be9-0108c17562a4%5C%22%3EMusk-level%20security%20can%20cost%20millions%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFormer%20Secret%20Service%20agent%20Joseph%20LaSorsa%2C%20who%20now%20runs%20the%20private%20security%20firm%20LaSorsa%20%26amp%3B%20Associates%2C%20previously%20told%20BI%20that%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsecurity-consultants-brian-thompson-unitedhealthcare-ceo-protection-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Earound-the-clock%20detail%20can%20cost%20%24100%2C000%20a%20month%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20isn't%20always%20enough%20to%20stop%20a%20motivated%20attacker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20those%20rates%2C%20the%20annual%20cost%20of%20protection%20could%20balloon%20to%20%241.2%20million%20%E2%80%94%20comparable%20to%20the%20base%20salaries%20of%20UnitedHealth's%20executive%20officers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20company-provided%20personal%20security%20can%20be%20an%20expensive%20proposition%2C%20and%20typically%20reserved%20only%20for%20a%20small%20number%20of%20top%20leaders.%20Different%20executives%20may%20also%20have%20their%20own%20personal%20preference%20for%20the%20level%20of%20security%20they%20travel%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BProtection%20is%20very%20much%20driven%20on%20what%20a%20executive%20really%20wants%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20John%20Orloff%2C%20a%20former%20US%20Secret%20Service%20agent%20who%20now%20leads%20security%20risk%20consulting%20at%20Jensen%20Hughes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOrloff%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20his%20firm%20typically%20works%20with%20corporate%20security%20departments%20to%20develop%20their%20executive%20protection%20strategies%20in%20response%20to%20relevant%20threats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%2C%20the%20world's%20wealthiest%20person%2C%20has%20spoken%20out%20about%20personal%20security%20concerns%20in%20recent%20years.%20He%20told%20Tesla%20shareholders%20at%20the%20annual%20shareholder%20meeting%20that%20%26quot%3Btwo%20homicidal%20maniacs%26quot%3B%20had%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-headquarters-terroristic-threat-austin-elon-musk-zach-kirkhorn-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ethreatened%20to%20kill%20him%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20things%20were%20%26quot%3Bgetting%20a%20little%20crazy%20these%20days.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Elon%20Musk%20enters%20the%20US%20Capitol%20to%20meet%20with%20lawmakers%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67532feb8fbb2783ed304a41%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EElon%20Musk%2C%20flanked%20by%20one%20of%20his%20security%20guards%2C%20enters%20the%20US%20Capitol%20to%20meet%20with%20lawmakers.%3Cp%3ESamuel%20Corum%2FGetty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFilings%20show%20Tesla%20paid%20a%20Musk-owned%20personal%20security%20company%20%242.4%20million%20to%20protect%20him%20in%202023.%20However%2C%20the%20agreement%20is%20not%20structured%20as%20compensation%20for%20his%20services%20as%20CEO%20and%20is%20unusual%20among%2